  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "It consists of a very simple description of sensor events and minimal instructions to the LLM.",
    "• ADL-LLM w/ absolute tss: An alternative version of the Window2Text approach generating textual representations using absolute timestamps instead of relative temporal relationships (e.g., \"after N minutes\").",
    "• ADL-LLM w/o CoT: Removed the Chain of Thought (CoT) reasoning from the system prompt (i.e., we removed the line \"reason step by step\").",
    "• ADL-LLM w/o Env: An alternative system prompt where we omitted the description of the environment (i.e., the rooms and the monitored household items).",
    "The results of this comparison are summarized in Table 5, while examples of prompts for the alternative approaches can be found in the appendix (supplemental material).Consistently with the results in the corresponding paper, the Cleland [17] approach exhibits poor results with a zero-shot strategy."
  ],
